<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3826.3.9>
    bibo:endPage "600" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "591" ;
    bibo:volume "3826" ;
    dc:creator "Wang, Zhu-Hong; Huang, Jian; Polaszek, Andrew" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Three new species of Baeoentedon Girault (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae) from China, with the first record of whitefly host association (Hemiptera: Aleyrodidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230324>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230325>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230326> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230324>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 8. Baeoentedon balios, female: 1, body showing gaster with T 1 – T 5 mostly pale yellow; 2, head and mesosoma; 3, antenna; 4, fore wing; 5, parastigma and submarginal vein; 6, stigmal vein; 7, ovipositor before slide-mounting; 8, ovipositor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/230324/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230325>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 11. Baeoentedon balios, male: 9, body showing gaster with T 1 and T 2 mostly pale yellow; 10, antenna; 11, male genitalia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/230325/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230326>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12 – 13. Pealius spina, a whitefly host association for Baeoentedon balios. 12, P. spina “ puparium ” parasitized by B. balios; 13, P. spina empty “ puparium ” (left) and emerged parasitoid, B. balios (right)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/230326/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

